<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="528" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1716,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1788,1814]" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Tobias, 1964" authorityName="Tobias" authorityYear="1964" box="[664,996,1788,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Chelonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sternalis" subGenus="Arichelonus">
<emphasis box="[664,690,1789,1815]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[706,731,1789,1815]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[746,842,1788,1814]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">sternalis</emphasis>
Tobias, 1964
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated from the latter by the following characters: length of metasoma 2.3 × its height (4.0 × in 
<taxonomicName authority="Tobias, 1964" authorityName="Tobias" authorityYear="1964" box="[965,1306,1824,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Chelonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="528" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sternalis" subGenus="Arichelonus">
<emphasis box="[965,991,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1009,1033,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1051,1147,1824,1850]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">sternalis</emphasis>
Tobias, 1964
</taxonomicName>
); scutellum coarsely reticulate rugose and punctate medially (smooth medially); antennomeres of female 18, length of antenna distinctly shorter than body length (antenna very slender and filiform, antennomeres 38, as long as body).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="529" pageId="1" pageNumber="528" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1716,2031]" box="[199,1068,1932,1959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1932,1958]" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[352,459,1932,1958]" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">Holotype</typeStatus>
, female, length of body 
<quantity box="[730,818,1933,1959]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="528" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.4 mm</quantity>
, of fore wing 
<quantity box="[975,1064,1933,1959]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="528" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1716,2031]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,933]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="529" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,1969,1995]" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">Head.</emphasis>
Antennomeres 18, basal half of left antenna distinctly broadened; third antennomere equal in length to fourth; third, fourth and terminal antennomeres 3.2 ×, 3.2 × and 2.3 × longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[1153,1233,2004,2031]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chelonus (Arichelonus) allokotosus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854030/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="528">Fig. 2I</figureCitation>
); head transverse, width of head 2.6 × its dorsal length roundly contracted behind eyes; OOL: OD: POL= 9: 4: 9; longitudinal diameter of eye 1.1 × height of temples; vertex behind ocelli and temple evenly convex, transversely striate; frons distinctly concave, smooth (
<figureCitation box="[355,445,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chelonus (Arichelonus) allokotosus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854030/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
); face coarsely striate-rugose; clypeus shiny, finely punctate with dense setae (
<figureCitation box="[1325,1415,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chelonus (Arichelonus) allokotosus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854030/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Length of mesosoma 1.4 × its height; pronotum finely reticulate-rugose; mesoscutum evenly convex, reticulate-rugose; scutellum hardly convex, more strongly and coarsely rugose than mesoscutum, punctate medially; scutellar suture comparatively deep, narrow, with carinae; apical transverse carina of propodeum short, near posterior margin of propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[517,605,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chelonus (Arichelonus) allokotosus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854030/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
); mesopleuron evenly convex, coarsely reticulate-rugose (
<figureCitation box="[1258,1346,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chelonus (Arichelonus) allokotosus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854030/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,282,402,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Wings.</emphasis>
Length of fore wing 2.6 × its width; length of marginal cell 1.25 × pterostigma; vein r straight, r: 3-SR: SR1 = 7: 7: 45; 1-CU1: 2-CU1= 6: 17 (
<figureCitation box="[592,682,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chelonus (Arichelonus) allokotosus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854030/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,475,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind coxa mainly smooth and shallowly punctate; hind coxa, femur and tibia all distinctly robust; length of hind femur, tibia and basitarsus 3.0 ×, 3.75 × and 3.8 × their maximum width, respectively (
<figureCitation box="[1210,1297,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chelonus (Arichelonus) allokotosus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854030/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,547,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Metasoma.</emphasis>
Carapace elongate-oval, but distinctly contracted at the one-third of apex, two thirds of it longitudinally striate, and reticulate by weaker and transverse rugae basally; length of carapace 2.3 × its maximum width in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[327,418,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chelonus (Arichelonus) allokotosus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854030/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
); ventrally metasoma completely open to apex of carapace; length of ovipositor projecting part 0.5 × of carapace length, and the ovipositor sheath 0.13 × as long as fore wing, 0.38 × as long as hind tibia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chelonus (Arichelonus) allokotosus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854030/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,726,752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Colour.</emphasis>
Black; antennomeres dark brown; palp blackish-brown; pterostigma and veins yellowish-brown; pterostigma and veins light brown; wing membrane hyaline; legs almost entirely yellowish-brown, basally hind tibia light yellow and apically black; ovipositor sheath brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,933]" box="[199,392,835,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,835,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="529">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
